    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A fine-grain marble quarried near Marble in Gunnison County, Colorado. Colorado Yule marble is usually pure white but can have pale gray clouds and/or creamy veins. Some regions of the marble belt have a pale blue-gray color. Colorado Yule has been used for statuary and was used for the exterior of the Lincoln Memorial.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
